A 20-year-old man has been arrested in connection with the death of another man in Glasgow. Man arrested over Stephen McGinlay death in Glasgow A 20-year-old man has been arrested in connection with the death of another man in Glasgow.
Stephen McGinlay, 26, from the city's Possilpark area, was found injured on St George's Road on 2 October.
He died three days later in hospital.
The arrested man is expected to appear at Glasgow Sheriff Court on Tuesday.
 